headlines.description: — Grant Williams dubbed himself “Batman” after he helped the Boston Celtics neutralize Nuggets star Nikola “Joker” Jokic during a win in Denver late last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 34, Celtics beat Nuggets for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Wendell Carter Jr. had 20 points and 10 rebounds, and the Orlando Magic beat the Phoenix Suns 114-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carter, Ross lead Magic to 114-97 win over Suns

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 30 points, Jalen Brunson added 26, and the New York Knicks held on to beat the Detroit Pistons, 121-112, on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: New York Knicks hold on for 121-112 win over Detroit Pistons

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Eugene Omoruyi scored a career-high 22 points to help the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Toronto Raptors 132-113 on Friday night to snap a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Omoruyi scores career-high 22 as Thunder top Raptors 132-113

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson scored 29 points, and the San Antonio Spurs stopped a five-game skid by topping the banged-up Milwaukee Bucks 111-93 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson leads Spurs past injury-riddled Bucks 111-93

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 28 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 114-103 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has 28 to power Grizzlies past Timberwolves, 114-103

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — As Stephen Curry approaches his mid-30s, Steve Kerr marvels at the superstar's fitness and his ability to continue to take over games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 40, Warriors rally past Mitchell, Cavs 106-101

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — One of De’Aaron Fox's goals coming into the season was to make sure he avoided a slow start.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 32, Kings deal Lakers 5th straight loss 120-114
